\begin_layout Standard
To be able to take photos, do the following: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 This feature is enabled by ensuring the value of $sysconf ['webcam'] =
 true; in the file sysconfig.inc.php 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
 Make sure your browser supports Flash player 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
3.
 Click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Load Camera
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
4.
 Click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Capture
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
5.
 Click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Use It!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
6.
 Don't forget to specify the file format and size 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As shown in the picture above, SLiMS provides two choices: take the direct
 image (pictured above) that facilitate members who forget to bring a digital
 photo, or upload an existing file photo.
\end_layout

