\begin_layout Section
Member Custom Field
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similar to the Biblio Custom field, using this feature Senayan users can
 add information (fields) that have to be filled in the membership information
 form.
 To add a new field, the steps are as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
• Open the member_custom_fields.inc.php file located in the folder /admin/modules/
membership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
• In this file there are 5 custom fields that can be used.
 Custom fields can be removed or reduced.
 For example, one new filed will be added to update the status of marriage,
 then custom 2-5 are uninstalled first.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The Custom Field 1 is completed as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout LyX-Code
'dbfield' => 'status', // name of field in 'biblio' table in database, make
 sure you already define it! 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'label' => __('Status Pernikahan'), // label of field in form 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'type' => 'text', // type of field 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'default' => '', // default value of field 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'max' => '50', // maximum character to enter in 'text' field type
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'data' => false, // an array of data for 'dropdown', 'checklist' or 'choice'
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'indexed' => true, // NOT APPLICABLE YET, FOR FUTURE RELEASE USE
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
'width' => 50), // width of field in form for 'text' field type, maximum
 is 100
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The next step is to add a field/column status in the member table .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The result of this modification is as follows (can be seen in Add New Member):
\end_layout

